TY  - JOUR
TI  - Money and Interest in a Cash-in-Advance Economy
AU  - Lucas, Robert E.
AU  - Stokey, Nancy L.
AB  - [In this paper we analyze an aggregate general equilibrium model in which the use of money is motivated by a cash-in-advance constraint, applied to purchases of a subset of consumption goods. The system is subject to both real and monetary shocks, which are economy-wide and observed by all. We develop methods for verifying the existence of, characterizing, and explicitly calculating equilibria.]
C1  - Full publication date: May, 1987
DB  - JSTOR
DO  - 10.2307/1913597
EP  - 513
